00:02:28.044 --> 00:02:28.878
What's that?

00:02:29.504 --> 00:02:30.380
A dragon?

00:02:31.297 --> 00:02:32.674
Baekjeong, my foot.

00:02:34.592 --> 00:02:35.718
Oh, it's a snake head.

00:02:35.802 --> 00:02:36.928
It's a chicken head.

00:02:37.011 --> 00:02:38.137
Seok-sam, that punk.

00:02:38.221 --> 00:02:40.890
His eyes lie just as much as his words do.

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:45.186
These herbs are good
for child malnutrition.

00:02:45.270 --> 00:02:47.689
There's no way
he saw this righteous thief.

00:02:47.772 --> 00:02:51.067
Well, how can a thief
possibly be righteous?

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:52.902
Do you really think so?

00:02:52.986 --> 00:02:54.362
The granaries of corrupt officials

00:02:54.445 --> 00:02:57.407
are filled with things
taken from the people.

00:02:57.490 --> 00:02:59.409
Which means those granaries

00:02:59.492 --> 00:03:00.868
rightfully belong to the people.

00:03:00.952 --> 00:03:02.620
So it isn't theft.

00:03:02.704 --> 00:03:05.623
It is merely giving back
what was taken from them.

00:03:05.707 --> 00:03:07.500
You heard him.

00:03:08.918 --> 00:03:11.504
Are you on the thief's side too, sir?

00:03:13.089 --> 00:03:16.467
How could I ever take a thief's side?
I'm only speaking the truth.

00:03:16.551 --> 00:03:19.137
Rumors are never wholly true.

00:03:20.430 --> 00:03:21.889
So maybe

00:03:21.973 --> 00:03:24.183
the name is fake.

00:03:25.435 --> 00:03:26.352
The name?

00:03:26.978 --> 00:03:29.147
People call him Gil-dong.

00:03:29.856 --> 00:03:31.149
"A friend on the road"?

00:03:32.442 --> 00:03:33.568
Is that what it means?

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:37.155
Well, some say that
it means "the rope on the ground."

00:03:38.489 --> 00:03:39.824
This is a real headache.

00:03:39.907 --> 00:03:42.452
The truth is lost amid countless rumors.

00:03:45.121 --> 00:03:46.748
-Did I just say…
-Did you just say…

00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:48.624
"lost"?

00:04:11.564 --> 00:04:12.982
YI YEOL
GRAND PRINCE DOWOL

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:16.235
I told you,

00:04:16.319 --> 00:04:19.322
when you're lost in the case,
you can always come to me.

00:04:22.367 --> 00:04:23.659
He has good ears.

00:04:23.743 --> 00:04:25.828
It's good to see you again,
Your Highness.

00:04:25.912 --> 00:04:27.121
It has been a long time.

00:04:29.248 --> 00:04:30.500
That said,

00:04:30.583 --> 00:04:34.128
the moral order has collapsed.
This is no small matter.

00:04:36.339 --> 00:04:38.132
Please have a seat here.

00:04:39.550 --> 00:04:42.303
I know we're both busy,
so let us dispense with formalities.

00:04:44.055 --> 00:04:45.848
And there is no need for thanks.

00:04:45.932 --> 00:04:49.602
This isn't the first time I've
shared my wisdom with you thick-heads.

00:04:51.354 --> 00:04:53.815
We are deeply grateful
for your constant help

00:04:53.898 --> 00:04:55.316
with our investigations.

00:04:59.278 --> 00:05:01.989
The great thief
who stole ten thousand seok of rice?

00:05:02.949 --> 00:05:04.659
-Who are the victims?
-There are none.

00:05:06.744 --> 00:05:09.080
Those crooked officials
couldn't come forward,

00:05:09.163 --> 00:05:10.832
afraid their own sins would be exposed.

00:05:10.915 --> 00:05:12.625
They just chose not to.

00:05:12.708 --> 00:05:15.753
-And I wouldn't either, if I were them.
-Why is that?

00:05:16.504 --> 00:05:18.881
Someone reported
that they saw Gil-dong here,

00:05:18.965 --> 00:05:20.383
at the Chief Censor's storehouse.

00:05:20.466 --> 00:05:21.300
That's right.

00:05:21.384 --> 00:05:24.720
One of our slaves
saw something suspicious.

00:05:32.270 --> 00:05:34.063
The storehouse is already full again.

00:05:34.147 --> 00:05:36.440
The Chief Censor
must be blessed with fortune,

00:05:36.524 --> 00:05:38.025
though he doesn't seem like it.

00:05:38.109 --> 00:05:39.110
Well, the truth is…

00:05:39.193 --> 00:05:41.070
You couldn't find anything stolen.

00:05:41.154 --> 00:05:44.115
That's right, sir.
Everything is exactly as it was.

00:05:44.699 --> 00:05:46.576
-Search the place.
-Yes, sir.

00:05:56.502 --> 00:05:57.753
I found it!

00:06:04.218 --> 00:06:06.429
It looks like a bowl of rice.

00:06:06.512 --> 00:06:10.057
-Did Gil-dong leave this drawing?
-Yes, Your Highness.

00:06:15.730 --> 00:06:16.856
Could it be…

00:06:18.357 --> 00:06:19.358
Weigh the rice now.

00:06:26.115 --> 00:06:27.325
How much is missing?

00:06:28.075 --> 00:06:32.330
One sack should fill an entire jar,
but exactly three does are missing.

00:06:34.123 --> 00:06:37.919
That means Gil-dong stole
just three does of rice.

00:06:38.002 --> 00:06:41.380
This is why his thefts
were usually discovered much later.

00:06:41.464 --> 00:06:45.259
And even when it's discovered,
the amount is too small to report.

00:06:46.427 --> 00:06:49.388
Has anyone claimed to have received
the stolen goods from Gil-dong?

00:06:49.472 --> 00:06:51.182
Not a single one.

00:06:53.309 --> 00:06:55.186
He's just a petty thief
who steals for himself.

00:06:55.269 --> 00:06:59.190
And people speak of him
as a righteous thief.

00:07:03.611 --> 00:07:04.445
Are there

00:07:05.321 --> 00:07:06.614
more of his drawings, like this?

00:07:08.491 --> 00:07:10.868
Why does he leave these drawings?

00:07:10.952 --> 00:07:13.079
If he didn't, no one would ever notice.

00:07:13.162 --> 00:07:14.580
That's what I'm talking about.

00:07:14.664 --> 00:07:16.749
It's like he's messing with us.

00:07:16.832 --> 00:07:18.042
Well, apparently,

00:07:18.125 --> 00:07:20.044
he's proud of his thefts.

00:07:20.753 --> 00:07:21.671
Humans, by nature,

00:07:21.754 --> 00:07:24.006
affirm their sense of worth
by revealing their strengths.

00:07:26.008 --> 00:07:27.093
Oh, I get it.

00:07:27.176 --> 00:07:29.262
Just like how you gather
all the court ladies to brag

00:07:29.345 --> 00:07:31.889
every time you solve a case.

00:07:33.307 --> 00:07:36.018
It means he's the kind of man
who craves attention as well.

00:07:36.102 --> 00:07:38.271
Is that a question or a criticism?

00:07:38.354 --> 00:07:40.022
I wouldn't dare. It's a mere question.

00:07:40.106 --> 00:07:41.774
No more questions from now on.

00:07:43.442 --> 00:07:45.820
I get why you spread out the drawings.

00:07:50.074 --> 00:07:51.033
Gil-dong wants

00:07:51.117 --> 00:07:53.911
to brag about his thefts everywhere.

00:07:55.246 --> 00:07:59.083
And there are rumors
calling him a righteous thief.

00:07:59.166 --> 00:08:01.419
He must be puffed up with pride.

00:08:01.919 --> 00:08:04.630
Well, who do you think
started those rumors?

00:08:04.714 --> 00:08:05.548
No way.

00:08:06.424 --> 00:08:07.300
Gil-dong.

00:08:09.802 --> 00:08:12.179
Seize those spreading the rumors.

00:08:12.263 --> 00:08:14.223
The false rumors
are covering up the thefts,

00:08:14.307 --> 00:08:16.183
so that's where we'll find the culprit.

00:08:16.267 --> 00:08:17.476
Yes, Your Highness.

00:08:19.937 --> 00:08:21.522
Your Highness,

00:08:21.606 --> 00:08:24.483
aren't you supposed to have tea
with the Queen Dowager around 4:00?

00:08:25.318 --> 00:08:26.736
Why are you saying that now?

00:08:26.819 --> 00:08:27.945
You said no more questions--

00:08:28.029 --> 00:08:30.489
Don't you know
how to say things as a statement?

00:08:51.010 --> 00:08:53.137
Hey, wake up.

00:08:54.055 --> 00:08:55.222
Wake up!

00:08:57.558 --> 00:08:58.768
Is His Majesty here?

00:08:58.851 --> 00:09:00.353
It's another Majesty!

00:09:00.436 --> 00:09:01.479
What?

00:09:03.189 --> 00:09:04.106
Your Majesty!

00:09:05.775 --> 00:09:07.276
Why did it have to be you?

00:09:07.360 --> 00:09:09.487
Couldn't you have made it
more convincing at least?

00:09:10.029 --> 00:09:12.114
